add python 3.6 unit test job

This is a mechanically generated patch to add a unit test job running
under Python 3.6 as part of the python3-first goal.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Story: #2002586
Task: #24312

commit_message:
This change allow setting kernel commandline args

- This change introduces a kernel_args parameter
  that allow setting of kernel commandline args.
- By default no addtional arguments will be set.

Implements: bp/kernel-hugepage-config
Implements: bp/ovs-dpdk

Change-Id: Id50e626f4eb19c47b59bccd392abe9559c650b38

LGFM'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-08-22 14:47:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

hi Long Zhang
there is no good singel way to test if dpdk is supproted by a host.

while hugepages are recommended not all dpdk applications actully need them. ovs-dpdk does. on intel platform either 1G or 2mb hugepages can be used to satisfy that requirement. generally i recommend 2MB hugepages. on ibm or arm plathforms you can use other hugepages sizes i belive one of those 2 plathforms supports 512mb hugepages.

as for cpu support the minimum instruction set requirement for dpdk to work is sse3. cat /proc/cpuinfo |grep pdpe1gb would tell me that i can allocate hugepages but not that they have been allocated. 

in any case this particular patch is not related to enabling dpdk really more serving a request to not require network manager on the host to configure the ip. to that end i am also adding the ablity to use systemd for this role as is supported already on centos.'}, {'account_id': 24043, 'date': '2017-08-22 16:04:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
make dpdk tunnel ip assignment configurable

- This change introduces a new variable to specify
  how to assign the local tunnel ip to a dpdk bridge.
- The valid values of dpdk_tunnel_interface_address_mode
  are native and systemd.
- The default behaviour is to use the native distro
  network manager on Debian family distros and systemd
  otherwise

Change-Id: Ib3788f49783159a360711165a176931e668814da
partial-implementes: bp/ovs-dpdk

commit_message:
snmp: listen on ctrlplane

Ceilometer uses the ctrlplane to poll snmpd on each
ironic node.

43155ed1462a8e27c9efdbb345bfc5832c50bd2f have restrict snmpd
to the internal_api subnet which breaks Ceilometer that use the
ctrlplane subnet.

This change puts the ctrlplane as default for snmpd.

Closes-bug: #1775001
Change-Id: Ia310e02d30ce037c2cc7fec146f27fbd0f8055f4
(cherry picked from commit b18e38c808ba4687fb4444ea3c7b02de44e4debb)
(cherry picked from commit 0b0a249ce075c43833ff0d037c8fc02c657dce6e)

commit_message:
Conditionalize rndc changes

The changes to allow configuration of more rndc options had a
cross-repo dependency on the tripleo-heat-templates changes that
made use of the new options.  Unfortunately, the puppet changes
landed first and are now broken because necessary inputs are not
being provided.  This change conditionalizes the new configurations
so that if the parameters aren't passed we won't attempt to do
invalid configuration.

Closes-Bug: #1788907
Change-Id: Ia82f1c6be0d5504498e77a90268cad8abecdeae2
(cherry picked from commit 3add939d4c723dec9cc1c2538ea28271d5769041)

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

'}]
commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I61e975791c9cfb920c389937eead436fa4966080

commit_message:
Fix notifier should only notify successfully evacuated nodes

Currently, Freezer' notifier when notifying about successful
evacuated nodes notifies all nodes.

    ...
    notify_nodes = evac.get_nodes_details(nodes)
    ...
    notifier.notify(notify_nodes, 'success')

Change-Id: I1f301b458a6407e5d98445707c00775ca730781f

commit_message:
Added NovaOVSDBConnection parameter

This parameter would be used by os-vif repo, this would
be used in ovs-vsctl commands to reach remote ovsdb over
tcp/ssl connection.

Signed-off-by: hanish gogada <hanishgogadahcu@gmail.com>

[{'created': '2018-08-24 23:28:12.000000000', 'message': "Deprecate Core/Ram/DiskFilter

The time has come.

These filters haven't been necessary since Ocata [1].
when the filter scheduler started using placement
to filter on VCPU, DISK_GB and MEMORY_MB. The
only reason to use them with any in-tree scheduler
drivers is if using the CachingScheduler which doesn't
use placement, but the CachingScheduler itself has
been deprecated since Pike [2]. Furthermore, as of
change [3] in Stein, the ironic driver no longer
reports vcpu/ram/disk inventory for ironic nodes
which will make these filters filter out ironic nodes
thinking they don't have any inventory. Also, as
noted in [4], the DiskFilter does not account for
volume-backed instances and may incorrectly filter
out a host based on disk inventory when it would
otherwise be OK if the instance is not using local
disk.

The related aggregate filters are left intact for
now, see blueprint placement-aggregate-allocation-ratios.

commit_message:
Deprecate Core/Ram/DiskFilter

The time has come.

These filters haven't been necessary since Ocata [1]
when the filter scheduler started using placement
to filter on VCPU, DISK_GB and MEMORY_MB. The
only reason to use them with any in-tree scheduler
drivers is if using the CachingScheduler which doesn't
use placement, but the CachingScheduler itself has
been deprecated since Pike [2]. Furthermore, as of
change [3] in Stein, the ironic driver no longer
reports vcpu/ram/disk inventory for ironic nodes
which will make these filters filter out ironic nodes
thinking they don't have any inventory. Also, as
noted in [4], the DiskFilter does not account for
volume-backed instances and may incorrectly filter
out a host based on disk inventory when it would
otherwise be OK if the instance is not using local
disk.

The related aggregate filters are left intact for
now, see blueprint placement-aggregate-allocation-ratios.

[1] Ie12acb76ec5affba536c3c45fbb6de35d64aea1b
[2] Ia7ff98ff28b7265058845e46b277317a2bfc96d2
[3] If2b8c1a76d7dbabbac7bb359c9e572cfed510800
[4] I9c2111f7377df65c1fc3c72323f85483b3295989

Change-Id: Id62136d293da55e4bb639635ea5421a33b6c3ea2
Related-Bug: #1787910

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I7abdeda5e90627776b588e196a72becfd599ebbf

messages:
[{'account_id': 26642, 'date': '2018-08-08 12:54:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2018-08-08 12:55:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

commit_message:
Fix first_execution_time when used together with pattern

When specifying pattern only in the API request, the returned
first_execution_time should be the calculated according to the pattern.

When specifying first_execution_time and pattern both in the API
request, the first_execution_time will be tweaked according to the
pattern.

Change-Id: I0c71c2d76584c9b8335d6b379361779191e8c8d2
Story: 2003483
Task: 24750

Using os-testr to get better report

for output and builds some helpful extra
functionality around testr

commit_message:
Skips signal handling on Windows

Setting up signal handling fails on Windows due to missing select
module attributes. This patch skips the setup on Windows.

Change-Id: I75db453ec907efb01e1bb411690dadd92a48314d
Closes-Bug: #1788022
(cherry picked from commit 2ee3894f49f315e35abff968f54ae72e5480e892)

commit_message:
Use user specified ssh key when removing tmp key

enable_ssh_admin was not using the user specified ssh key when removing
the generated tmp key. This could result in a permission denied error.

Change-Id: I3bd4ed6c58d6bffef811ee7ebc317056b34f2d3c
Closes-Bug: #1785704

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-06-07 16:45:07.000000000', 'message': 'fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I3492f6f9061a08d28bfde1a1ea1bc820c2b082c8
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
'}, {'created': '2018-08-21 12:55:46.000000000', 'message': 'fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Also update pylint to 1.9.2.

Change-Id: I3492f6f9061a08d28bfde1a1ea1bc820c2b082c8
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Also update pylint to 1.9.2.

Change-Id: I3492f6f9061a08d28bfde1a1ea1bc820c2b082c8
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
Signed-off-by: Chuck Short <chucks@redhat.com>

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Collect volume read/write bytes/requests

There is no volume read/write bytes/requests in the
ceilometer current master branch. When volume is attached
to the instance resource, it can get the device name of
the volume by metadata information, so volume
read/write bytes/requests information can be getted.

Change-Id: I07c676c1ba5eb2e0be55845e33d74a26c15f5f1e

commit_message:
Trivial: Move platform independent modules to common dir

async_process.py and ovsdb_monitor.py are now platform
independent, for which reason we can move them to
neutron/agent/common.

Note that a few subprojects are using async_process. We'll use
debtcollector so that we don't break those projects, while logging
a deprecation warning.

Change-Id: I6a7418cb8680cd71fe16c5d98b9b09ef2d260d37

commit_message:
Fixes for baremetal compute commands

Gather facts prior to using the stackhpc.os-shade role. This is required
following a recent change in that role to reference the ansible_user_uid and
ansible_user_gid facts.

Allow 'kayobe baremetal compute rename' command to ignore compute nodes in the
ansible inventory but not found in ironic.

Change-Id: I75a2f0dd0192e41de7b91376bb32b4149df04a60
TrivialFix

commit_message:
Pin Ansible Galaxy dependencies

Currently kayobe's ansible galaxy dependencies are unpinned. For
versioned roles, any new release will be picked up. For unversioned
roles, any new commit to master will be picked up. This is clearly not
ideal for stability, and we should pin these dependencies to specific
versions to avoid things changing under our feet. For unversioned roles,
we may want to consider adding versioning where we have the power to do
so.

Change-Id: Ib83a0d95b9061b3a57cb0e7c4cff3488ee076664
Story: 2003437
Task: 24633

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-20 16:30:31.000000000', 'message': "RabbitMQ upgrade fails due to stale /etc/hosts

This bug was previously fixed but the fix did not cover all cases. This
issue is still present if an IP address other than 127.0.0.1 or the
admin IP address (but not the internal API IP address, which is correct)
is in /etc/hosts. For example, in CI we often see 127.0.1.1.

This change removes all entries from /etc/hosts for the host's current
hostname, other than the internal API IP address. It also adds a call to
rabbitmqctl status to verify that the change has worked.

Related: We ought to improve the kolla ansible prechecks to catch the
case when there is more than one IP address mapping for the host's
current hostname.

Change-Id: I2cb9928e04005c6961f3de7c571c9a06361c4f23
Story: 2003496
Task: 24773
"}]
commit_message:
RabbitMQ upgrade fails due to stale /etc/hosts

This bug was previously fixed but the fix did not cover all cases. This
issue is still present if an IP address other than 127.0.0.1 or the
admin IP address (but not the internal API IP address, which is correct)
is in /etc/hosts. For example, in CI we often see 127.0.1.1.

This change removes all entries from /etc/hosts for the host's current
hostname, other than the internal API IP address. It also adds a call to
rabbitmqctl status to verify that the change has worked.

Related: We ought to improve the kolla ansible prechecks to catch the
case when there is more than one IP address mapping for the host's
current hostname.

Change-Id: I2cb9928e04005c6961f3de7c571c9a06361c4f23
Story: 2003496
Task: 24773

commit_message:
Fix kayobe overcloud service config save

If Kolla Ansible config files are not readable by the kayobe (stack)
user, the command will fail. This is fixed by using become.

Also improves the command output, by showing only the path of each file
rather than the full stat result.

Change-Id: I466e6a75822a1b2d2f91c9fadc9730c2cdb5bba0
TrivialFix

"}, {'created': '2018-08-08 16:21:22.000000000', 'message': "Fix stable/pike branch

Multiple fixes required for the stable/pike branch. All squashed into
one commit to ensure that Zuul checks can pass.

---

Fix ironic inspector rule registration

Use a specific inspector API version (1.12, the latest in Queens) to
ensure that new releases of ironic inspector don't break rule
registration.

This was happening because the client object created in the
os_ironic_inspector_rule module uses the maximum API version known to
the client.

Story: 2003129
Task: 23250
(cherry picked from commit f0b84702ee196648325ed90fd3c6a1199f6c0602)

---

Add missing Kolla Ansible group ironic-ipxe

Support for ipxe was backported to the default stackhpc/pike branch of
kolla ansible, so we need to at least define the group here.

---

Fix permissions of kolla-ansible target virtualenv

When using a target virtual environment for kolla-ansible [1], it is possible
to get a Permission Denied error. This can occur if the permissions of
/opt/kayobe or /opt/kayobe/venvs are restricted to the stack user (0700), since
kolla ansible uses the kolla user.

Although it makes sense for /opt/kayobe/venvs/kayobe to be 0700, /opt/kayobe
and /opt/kayobe/venvs should be 0755 to allow the kolla user to access a
virtualenv in /opt/kayobe/venvs/kolla-ansible.

This was seen during deployment of a seed, with kayobe target virtualenvs [2]
also in use. Since the kayobe-target-venv.yml playbook is one of the first
playbooks to be run, it will create the /opt/kayobe and /opt/kayobe/venvs
directories, and set the permissions correctly.

[1] http://kayobe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration/kolla-ansible.html#remote-execution-environment
[2] http://kayobe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration/kayobe.html#remote-execution-environment

Story: 2001968
Task: 15868

---

Fix yamllint issues in kolla-openstack role

---

Change-Id: I8c15cd874e147545b0604427771d412b482e5380

commit_message:
Fix stable/pike branch

Multiple fixes required for the stable/pike branch. All squashed into
one commit to ensure that Zuul checks can pass.

---

Fix ironic inspector rule registration

Use a specific inspector API version (1.12, the latest in Queens) to
ensure that new releases of ironic inspector don't break rule
registration.

This was happening because the client object created in the
os_ironic_inspector_rule module uses the maximum API version known to
the client.

Story: 2003129
Task: 23250
(cherry picked from commit f0b84702ee196648325ed90fd3c6a1199f6c0602)

---

Add missing Kolla Ansible group ironic-ipxe

Support for ipxe was backported to the default stackhpc/pike branch of
kolla ansible, so we need to at least define the group here.

---

Fix permissions of kolla-ansible target virtualenv

When using a target virtual environment for kolla-ansible [1], it is possible
to get a Permission Denied error. This can occur if the permissions of
/opt/kayobe or /opt/kayobe/venvs are restricted to the stack user (0700), since
kolla ansible uses the kolla user.

Although it makes sense for /opt/kayobe/venvs/kayobe to be 0700, /opt/kayobe
and /opt/kayobe/venvs should be 0755 to allow the kolla user to access a
virtualenv in /opt/kayobe/venvs/kolla-ansible.

This was seen during deployment of a seed, with kayobe target virtualenvs [2]
also in use. Since the kayobe-target-venv.yml playbook is one of the first
playbooks to be run, it will create the /opt/kayobe and /opt/kayobe/venvs
directories, and set the permissions correctly.

[1] http://kayobe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration/kolla-ansible.html#remote-execution-environment
[2] http://kayobe.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration/kayobe.html#remote-execution-environment

Story: 2001968
Task: 15868

---

Fix yamllint issues in kolla-openstack role

---

Pin Ansible Galaxy dependencies

Fixes a number of issues with galaxy roles that have moved on:

* Use specific versions of stackhpc.libvirt-vm and
  stackhpc.libvirt-host, the current master of these roles requires
  Ansible 2.4+.
* mrlesmithjr.manage-lvm changed the format of the disk list from
  comma-separated to a list.

Story: 2003437
Task: 24633

---

Use stable/pike branch of dev-kayobe-config

This will protect us against incompatible changes to the master branch
of that repo.

---

Change-Id: I8c15cd874e147545b0604427771d412b482e5380

It seems we currently only install ansible-pacemaker when we upgrade
the undercloud. This makes little sense because if you then happen
to do a minor update without first running undercloud upgrade you will
be welcomed by the following error:
u'TASK [include]
*****************************************************************',
 u'Thursday 09 August 2018  06:55:47 -0400 (0:00:00.388)
 0:00:10.970 ******* ',
  u'fatal: [controller-2]: FAILED! => {"failed": true, "reason": "no
  action detected in task. This often indicates a misspelled module
  name, or incorrect module path.\\n\\nThe error appears to have been in

While we do state that the undercloud should always be fully

commit_message:
WIP Install ansible-pacemaker by default

It seems we currently only install ansible-pacemaker when we upgrade
the undercloud. This makes little sense because if you then happen
to do a minor update without first running undercloud upgrade you will
be welcomed by the following error:
u'TASK [include]
*****************************************************************',
 u'Thursday 09 August 2018  06:55:47 -0400 (0:00:00.388)
 0:00:10.970 ******* ',
  u'fatal: [controller-2]: FAILED! => {"failed": true, "reason": "no
  action detected in task. This often indicates a misspelled module
  name, or incorrect module path.\\n\\nThe error appears to have been in
  \'/var/lib/mistral/dd74d929-9322-44ba-817a-e6e2a4792169/Controller/update_tasks.yaml\':

While we do state that the undercloud should always be fully
updated before running a minor update (or major upgrade), this
seems just a very unfriendly way of erroring out.

Dmitry, speaking of Actions, in BIOS patch I'm refactoring common.py to have basic ActionField with target_uri, but that is not reviewed and merged yet. 

But if we are going to reuse ActionField, should this refactoring be splitted in a separate super-small patch and merged as priority so that we both can use new ActionField in virtual media and BIOS patch?

For virtual media EjectMedia action is the simple one without parms, so it would be of type ActionField. 
InsertMedia has args, and could inherit from ActionField.

(see, https://review.openstack.org/#/c/570890/3/sushy/resources/common.py)"}, {'account_id': 26340, 'date': '2018-06-07 13:55:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

@Aleksandra thanks for your information. I was under the impression that DMTF standard hasn't yet released the Virtual Media related Actions API. Now that I can see it from your specified link: https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/VirtualMedia.v1_2_0.json 

I presume that the body would be something like this:

    "Actions": {
      "#VirtualMedia.InsertMedia": {
        "target": "/redfish/v1/Managers/1/VirtualMedia/CD1/Actions/VM.InsertMedia"
        },
      "#VirtualMedia.EjectMedia": {
        "target": "/redfish/v1/Managers/1/VirtualMedia/CD1/Actions/VM.EjectMedia"
        }
    }

Any idea whether there's any handy mockup available to validate these Action APIs? Thank you!'}, {'account_id': 16635, 'date': '2018-07-17 06:34:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

(2 comments)

No change in tests/ to remove the previously defined tasks? How can we make sure this works then?

Even if it's a backport, this seems incomplete."}, {'account_id': 23163, 'date': '2018-07-18 12:05:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> (2 comments)
 > 
 > No change in tests/ to remove the previously defined tasks? How can
 > we make sure this works then?
 > 
 > Even if it's a backport, this seems incomplete.

I don't understand. This is a backport. Even if we fix master, this still has to go in Queens as a backport before the fixes you requested are applied to the master and then backported. Or do you suggest to fork the backport?"}, {'account_id': 17068, 'date': '2018-07-18 12:16:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> > (2 comments)
 > >
 > > No change in tests/ to remove the previously defined tasks? How
 > can
 > > we make sure this works then?
 > >
 > > Even if it's a backport, this seems incomplete.
 > 
 > I don't understand. This is a backport. Even if we fix master, this
 > still has to go in Queens as a backport before the fixes you
 > requested are applied to the master and then backported. Or do you
 > suggest to fork the backport?

I am suggesting a combined backport.
For me we are adding tasks into a stable branch, with no coverage, which is something I'd like to avoid.

What I meant above is that we have new tasks, and a change in template -- how did it work before without those tasks?
Were those tasks included in the test case plays? Was there any config_template var doing the same work?

When I have an answer on those questions, I'll be able to review in more details, but my opinion is the following with the information I have:
- If it's a config_template change, is there a need to change it in the stable branch? I don't see one right now, at least not without a release note.
- If those tasks are included in tests, why is there no removal of the cruft? If no removal of those tasks of testing, they could still mask good behavior of the introduced tasks in the stable branch.

All of this is not "good enough" for me, and needs further work before it can be merged.'}, {'account_id': 23163, 'date': '2018-07-19 10:35:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 16011, 'date': '2018-08-01 21:30:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I don't think this is ever being hit."}, {'account_id': 23163, 'date': '2018-08-28 09:16:43.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

I don't think we need this anymore"}]

commit_message:
Public n/w access for vxlan tenant n/w in ml2.ovs

Currently neutron role doesn't configure l3 agent (controller) for
external network connecitivity for the openstack tenant network.
This needs some manual configuration to provide public network
access for the tenant VMs. This review attempts to automate these
steps.

Change-Id: I653ee5136ac508c473cbdb761a00454a774a4336
Signed-off-by: Periyasamy Palanisamy <periyasamy.palanisamy@ericsson.com>
(cherry picked from commit 452a2b668bb4a3ac6299fd99233bf7a813b095f9)

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I0755516a64149f75165ca33fbd6db0a2222027d6

commit_message:
Do not require username/password when enrolling Redfish nodes

While nearly always present, these fields are not required by ironic,
so we should not require them as well. This simplifies testing on
an emulator.

Change-Id: I8e7ce2312342c0572d5ba8967e4b7ac47d8401da
Closes-Bug: #1786976

[{'created': '2018-08-27 15:34:58.000000000', 'message': "privsep: Handle ENOENT when checking for direct IO support

We've seen an issue in some cloud providers [1] that suggest direct IO
support checks can fail in other ways. In those cases, the tests are
failing with FileNotFoundError, which is a Python 3-only exception type.
Fortunately we can mimic this by looking for IOError and checking the
errno attribute of same. This is what we do.

[1] http://status.openstack.org/elastic-recheck/#1788922

Change-Id: I8aab86bb62cbc8ad538c706af037a30437c7964d
Closes-Bug: #1788922

We've seen a recent issue [1] that suggest direct IO support checks can
fail in other ways. In those cases, the tests are failing with
FileNotFoundError, which is a Python 3-only exception type. Fortunately
we can mimic this by looking for checking for the errno attribute of the
OSError exception. This is what we do.

[1] http://status.openstack.org/elastic-recheck/#1788922

Change-Id: I8aab86bb62cbc8ad538c706af037a30437c7964d
Closes-Bug: #1788922
"}, {'created': '2018-08-27 16:05:37.000000000', 'message': "privsep: Handle ENOENT when checking for direct IO support

We've seen a recent issue that suggest direct IO support checks can fail
in other valid ways than EINVAL, namely, failures with ENOENT or the
FileNotFoundError exception, which is a Python 3-only exception type,
can occur. While we can't test for this without breaking Python 2.7
support, we can mimic this by looking for checking for the errno
attribute of the OSError exception. Do this.

Change-Id: I8aab86bb62cbc8ad538c706af037a30437c7964d
Closes-Bug: #1788922

commit_message:
privsep: Handle ENOENT when checking for direct IO support

We've seen a recent issue that suggest direct IO support checks can fail
in other valid ways than EINVAL, namely, failures with ENOENT or the
FileNotFoundError exception, which is a Python 3-only exception type,
can occur. While we can't test for this without breaking Python 2.7
support, we can mimic this by looking for checking for the errno
attribute of the OSError exception. Do this.

Change-Id: I8aab86bb62cbc8ad538c706af037a30437c7964d
Closes-Bug: #1788922

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

The legacy-tempest-dsvm-full-kafka job is only used by this plugin, so
we move the playbook and job definition here as well. It needs to be
renamed in order to be moved and applied to the repository, so the new
name devstack-plugin-kafka-tempest-full is used to indicate that it is
defined within the repository.

Change-Id: Ib043b0789b9f8e87e55799ced0d83b3391d98b72
Story: #2003250

[{'created': '2018-08-17 18:32:49.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: Make instance_list perform per-cell batching

I stopped short of committing to any configuration option in this
so maybe we can discuss. Some ideas:

- Just a boolean, where we batch at a fixed size if enabled
- A batch size, which we use if set, else no batching
- A batch size, determined as a fraction of the total limit plus
  some percentage, calculated by the count of cells. So, 10 cells
  and limit of 1000 means we batch at (1000/10)+10% or something.
  This requires getting a list of cells cached at some point so
  we know how large.
- A divisor (plus percentage?) of the total limit to use for the
  batch size, instead of "number of cells".

Change-Id: Ie3a5f5dc49f8d9a4b96f1e97f8a6ea0b5738b768

'}, {'created': '2018-08-20 17:42:16.000000000', 'message': 'Make instance_list perform per-cell batching

This makes the instance_list module support batching across cells
with a couple of different strategies, and with room to add more
in the future.

Before this change, an instance list with limit 1000 to a
deployment with 10 cells would generate a query to each cell
database with the same limit. Thus, that API request could end
up processing up to 10,000 instance records despite only
returning 1000 to the user (because of the limit).

This builds on the previous patch to support batching generically
in the multi_cell_list by providing a couple of strategies by
which the batch size per cell can be determined. These should
provide a lot of gain in the short term, and we can extend them
with other strategies as we identify some with additional
benefits.

Closes-Bug: #1787977
Change-Id: Ie3a5f5dc49f8d9a4b96f1e97f8a6ea0b5738b768

commit_message:
Make instance_list perform per-cell batching

This makes the instance_list module support batching across cells
with a couple of different strategies, and with room to add more
in the future.

Before this change, an instance list with limit 1000 to a
deployment with 10 cells would generate a query to each cell
database with the same limit. Thus, that API request could end
up processing up to 10,000 instance records despite only
returning 1000 to the user (because of the limit).

This uses the batch functionality in the base code added in
Iaa4759822e70b39bd735104d03d4deec988d35a1
by providing a couple of strategies by which the batch size
per cell can be determined. These should provide a lot of gain
in the short term, and we can extend them with other strategies
as we identify some with additional benefits.

Closes-Bug: #1787977
Change-Id: Ie3a5f5dc49f8d9a4b96f1e97f8a6ea0b5738b768

I don't know the history of all that, so I'm not sure I understand the nuances, but thought it worth mentioning."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-10 14:44:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Chris tested this in his perf harness yesterday [1] and the slow-down with this split-out was negligible (<0.5%, which may even be within the bounds of normal variance).

[1] http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-placement/%23openstack-placement.2018-08-09.log.html#t2018-08-09T16:10:43'}, {'account_id': 4690, 'date': '2018-08-10 14:52:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

> wfm.
 > 
 > One thing we might want to consider is if all these log messages
 > should be at level debug. Given what people have said on the
 > related email thread, people (sadly) want this all the time but
 > there are mixed messages about whether logging should be set to
 > debugging always. I don't know the history of all that, so I'm not
 > sure I understand the nuances, but thought it worth mentioning.

I think they should be at level debug based on my experience working on a large-scale deployment at my last company. We weren't able to run the scheduler at log level DEBUG all the time because it slowed the scheduler down significantly. So logging all of that at INFO, I would be wary of. That said, I'm not sure what the differences would be in this particular case DEBUG vs INFO. Maybe it's not nearly as significant as it was in the scheduler filters case."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-10 16:07:31.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5: Patch Set 4 was rebased.'}, {'account_id': 23498, 'date': '2018-08-10 17:21:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
[placement] split gigantor SQL query, add logging

This patch modifies the code paths for the non-granular request group
allocation candidates processing. It removes the giant multi-join SQL
query and replaces it with multiple calls to
_get_providers_with_resource(), logging the number of matched providers
for each resource class requested and filter (on required traits,
forbidden traits and aggregate memebership).

Here are some examples of the debug output:

- A request for three resources with no aggregate or trait filters:

 found 7 providers with available 5 VCPU
 found 9 providers with available 1024 MEMORY_MB
 found 5 providers after filtering by previous result
 found 8 providers with available 1500 DISK_GB
 found 2 providers after filtering by previous result

- The same request, but with a required trait that nobody has, shorts
  out quickly:

 found 0 providers after applying required traits filter (['HW_CPU_X86_AVX2'])

- A request for one resource with aggregates and forbidden (but no
  required) traits:

 found 2 providers after applying aggregates filter ([['3ed8fb2f-4793-46ee-a55b-fdf42cb392ca']])
 found 1 providers after applying forbidden traits filter ([u'CUSTOM_TWO', u'CUSTOM_THREE'])
 found 3 providers with available 4 VCPU
 found 1 providers after applying initial aggregate and trait filters

Co-authored-by: Eric Fried <efried@us.ibm.com>
Closes-Bug: #1786519
Change-Id: If9ddb8a6d2f03392f3cc11136c4a0b026212b95b

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I84f670a339f8540d1a65a666d810ad4c546eb48f

commit_message:
mysql/client: create tripleo.cnf everytime

If TLS isn't enabled, Augeas won't create tripleo.cnf but Docker will
create the file itself while mount binding it into the container.
With podman, the files/dirs that don't exist aren't created (probably
for the best), so let's create this empty file so podman can mount it
anyway.

Blueprint podman-support
Co-Authored-By: Cdric Jeanneret <cjeanner@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I28fa68f5a802ad60a2cac0dd2644804dd1f47e9e

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so the "-u root -p" is useless.

Change-Id: I525a3fdb77f1dfc93d87cc5fe619315d36e7004d
Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I62b44b25f8027845d871cc9b4ac62e51a558a07e

commit_message:
snmp: listen on ctrlplane

Ceilometer uses the ctrlplane to poll snmpd on each
ironic node.

43155ed1462a8e27c9efdbb345bfc5832c50bd2f have restrict snmpd
to the internal_api subnet which breaks Ceilometer that use the
ctrlplane subnet.

This change puts the ctrlplane as default for snmpd.

Closes-bug: #1775001
Change-Id: Ia310e02d30ce037c2cc7fec146f27fbd0f8055f4
(cherry picked from commit b18e38c808ba4687fb4444ea3c7b02de44e4debb)

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: Id03f88fbfa569bac36e61c457f3b8a17218f0519

commit_message:
Fix neutron-openvswitch-agent Windows support

Currently, the neutron-openvswitch-agent does not start on Windows
due to Linux specific imports. This patch addresses this issue.

Also, we're wrapping the object returned by subprocess.Popen using
tpool.Proxy in order to prevent IO operations on the stream
handles from blocking other threads. Currently, the ovs db monitor
blocks the whole process.

Closes-Bug: #1775382

Co-Authored-By: Lucian Petrut <lpetrut@cloudbasesolutions.com>
Change-Id: I8bbc9d1f8332e5644a6071f599a7c6a66bef7928

commit_message:
List instances from all cells explicitly

This is a minor refactor with no functional change that will make
the next patch easier. If we're not limiting cell scope during an
instance list, we just let context.scatter_gather_all_cells() load
and use the global list of cells. Since we will want to count
those cells and adjust the batch size, we might as well just always
pass in the list of cells, which will either be a subset or all
of them.

Change-Id: Id167ab6d01698878d783999d54bcf77f37eec020

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I7858563bbac2cf74bb10c3af5d0809fac0e4920f

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I58a334c36c010b254a1890e44a2b578dfdf7ff95

commit_message:
Fix no ACCEPT event can get for security group logging

Currently, we cannot get ACCEPT packet log because there are some
changed related to ovs firewall code since ovs firewall logging has
been merged.

Regarding to performance perspective, we only log first accepted packet.
So we only need to forward first accepted packet of each connection
session to table 91 and table 92.

So this patch fixes these issues.

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I115c256b07894f59f11a43c7bdb2cf75863265eb

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: Ib796d78fe15f4706dae98dabdae3b1ff5a6d318d

commit_message:
Always enable image prepare service for docker clouds

This change includes the service
OS::TripleO::Services::ContainerImagePrepare by default in the overcloud
which will trigger a container image prepare in the same way as is
currently done for the containerized undercloud.

Along with the mistral action which populates the container image
parameters, this change makes blueprint container-prepare-workflow
functionally complete.

Change-Id: I8b0c5e630e63ef6a2e6f70f1eb00fd02f4cfd1c0
Blueprint: container-prepare-workflow

commit_message:
Conditionalize rndc changes

The changes to allow configuration of more rndc options had a
cross-repo dependency on the tripleo-heat-templates changes that
made use of the new options.  Unfortunately, the puppet changes
landed first and are now broken because necessary inputs are not
being provided.  This change conditionalizes the new configurations
so that if the parameters aren't passed we won't attempt to do
invalid configuration.

Closes-Bug: #1788907
Change-Id: Ia82f1c6be0d5504498e77a90268cad8abecdeae2

commit_message:
Update error string to be unicode

We need to be more explicit for python3 that the string is a unicode
string. Otherwise it fails with:

TypeError: a bytes-like object is required, not 'str'

This was a side effect of the patch to address the stdout parsing under
python3. See Id0060a3abbcda8edb6124eb096cb824aaea48396

Change-Id: Ib6dd969dd24c0624028e09fac5abea29f7efa870
Related-Blueprint: python3-support

The spec of Zaqar mail delivery

This work is aimed to enable Zaqar to send email subscription
without the third part tools.

commit_message:
Introduce QuotaEngine

Introduce QuotaEngine and quota drivers. QuotaEngine
is the core of quota support feature.
* Register resources and its usages.
* Get project quotas.
* Create and update project quotas.

Change-Id: I055c310439354a9ebe69dad480494ac35207252f
Partial-Implements: blueprint quota-support

commit_message:
Add fullstack test to restart agent with active l3-ha router

Re-start of the l3 agent hosting the active l3-ha router
shouldn't cause data plane interruption, assuming there
is no failover.  Create a test explicitly for that.

Change-Id: I5963c21e2b382a09c40b81e2446350696e16d265
Related-Bug: #1776459

Switch to stestr

According to Openstack summit session [1],
stestr is maintained project to which all Openstack projects should migrate.
Let's switch to stestr as other projects have already moved to it.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/YVR-python-pti

commit_message:
Bump ceph_client

The ceph_client role could no longer deploy because EPEL was pulled
out.  We fixed this in a patch but we need to make sure it's part
of the deliverable.

Depends-On: Ib0fe5c8d89c5743d9dfd7da2913862aac7d75946

commit_message:
Move MFA receipt specification to Stein

This work was staged for Rocky but wasn't completed. This commit
reproposes it to Stein to keep the Rocky specs directory accurate.

[{'created': '2018-07-06 08:16:25.000000000', 'message': 'Reuse SSH connections for executing multiple commands.

When using SSH client to execute a command a paramiko
client is created, it is connected to server and then the
client and it is forgot without closing socket.

This produces a leak of SSH connections. It also slow
down test executions when more than one command has to
be executed with the same SSH client (for example when
executing ping from remote VM).

This change also add convenience methods to SSH client.

- connect() method allows to create and connect paramiko
  client to be used by tests directly (for exaple to open
  a command like socat, cat, nc and redirect STDIN/STDOUT
  to generate or receive network traffic.
- close() method allow to close paramiko client socket and
  release resources.
- execute_script() spawn a script interpreter (Bash by default) on
  a remote machinge to execute a script provided as a string.
  For convenience by default it combines STDOUT and STDERR to LOG
  an human friendly message when the script fails.

Change-Id: I3a70131f03aea342c8e8a04038000bd974cca921

commit_message:
Reuse SSH connections for executing multiple commands.

When using SSH client to execute a command a Paramiko
client is created, it is connected to server and then the
client reference is forgot without closing socket.

This produces a leak of SSH connections. It also slow
down test executions when more than one command has to
be executed with the same SSH client (for example when
executing ping between VMs).

This change also add convenience methods to SSH client:

- connect() method allows to create and connect Paramiko
  client to be used by tests directly (for exaple to open
  a command like socat, cat, nc and redirect STDIN/STDOUT
  to generate or receive network traffic. The method is
  going to return the same Paramiko client instance
  until close() method is called.

- close() method allows to close paramiko client socket and
  release resources.

- execute_script() spawn a script interpreter (Bash by default) on
  a remote machinge to execute a script provided as a string.
  For convenience by default it combines STDOUT and STDERR to LOG
  an human friendly message when the script fails.

Change-Id: I3a70131f03aea342c8e8a04038000bd974cca921

commit_message:
Fix README

A new configuration option for the s3token middleware called auth_uri can
be used to set the URI to be used for authentication. This replaces
auth_host, auth_port, and auth_protocol.
The auth_host, auth_port, and auth_protocol configuration options to the
s3token middleware are now deprecated.

Change-Id: Ia85d2c8fceeca72ca617f4f34047b7d9d379e39b

commit_message:
Update glance packages name for Fedora

For services starting from Fedora, RPM specs from [1]
and repos [2] would be used. Do necessary changes in
glance packages names.

Also do not hard code packages name, instead take them
from glance::params.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/rpm-packaging/blob/master/openstack/glance/glance.spec.j2
[2] https://trunk.rdoproject.org/fedora/current/

Change-Id: Ibee5776116ebecf9f1e28632c4ab6317075ca868

commit_message:
Introduce --default-runtime parameter

Default to 'docker', --default-runtime will allow us to change the
runtime (docker, podman, etc) in the future.
In future patches, we'll add support for LibPod and this patch will
allow to start running "paunch apply" for a specific runtime backend.

Change-Id: I4660f37a3fc231830f4f3a875f63473d68ca7cfc

commit_message:
add lower-constraints job

Create a tox environment for running the unit tests against the lower
bounds of the dependencies.

Create a lower-constraints.txt to be used to enforce the lower bounds
in those tests.

Add openstack-tox-lower-constraints job to the zuul configuration.

See http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-March/128352.html
for more details.

Change-Id: Ie87b5f50bab2e930e571f0177f6dc259ca0f4596
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/555034
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
Co-Authored-By: Nguyen Hai <nguyentrihai93@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Only add --no-site-packages when necessary

The --no-site-packages option is deprecated, and is only
necessary for virtualenv versions below 1.7.0. This patch
checks the version and adds it only when necessary.

Change-Id: I19b4acf148c28c96f58bcbda4b19153d56206008
(cherry picked from commit 94c6e3ff99d651068def942828f7d715322dae0a)

commit_message:
Upgrade pip/setuptools/wheel in the venv

To ensure a uniform experience across distributions
and from build to build, we need to ensure that the
venv has a consistent version of pip, setuptools and
wheel. This patch ensures that these packages are
upgraded to the latest version allowed by the args
provided.

This prevents issues as discovered and solved by
https://review.openstack.org/596553

We also remove the virtualenv_site_packages argument
from the pip tasks as they are unnecessary given that
the virtualenv is created in an earlier task.

Change-Id: Ia9e2f695212b01a54f8e73fbd03faa8e9b492f93
(cherry picked from commit 8f1129e9899e1ed3cf3fc5f06cb93b84f91bc651)

commit_message:
Only add --no-site-packages when necessary

The --no-site-packages option is deprecated, and is only
necessary for virtualenv versions below 1.7.0. This patch
checks the version and adds it only when necessary.

Change-Id: I19b4acf148c28c96f58bcbda4b19153d56206008

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I9fa737702c29438a47d572a1c480714c17b4d0d2
Story: #2002586
Task: #24322

commit_message:
Adjust tenacity mock

Recent changes in tenacity have broken how we mock the wait call for the
test. This change mocks out the inspect.getargspec call that is used in
tenacity to fix our unit tests for now. I think it might be beneficial
to not actually test the retry functionality in the tripleo-common unit
tests as it seems to be more of a test for tenacity than tripleo-common.

Closes-Bug: #1788802

commit_message:
[log] Add 'firewall_group' as a loggable resource type for logging

Currently, OSC plugin for logging only supports security group as
a loggable resource. This patch aims to add 'firewall_group' as a
supported resource type.

Co-Authored-By: Van Hung Pham <HungPV@vn.fujitsu.com>
Depends-On: Ie10063197f02679e987e87cb4852f5230a02f76d
Change-Id: I2ac92004c2ad3769c9749e131718a8ef0003c4bd
Partial-Bug: #1720727

commit_message:
Correct cache_valid_time variable name

The variable name is venv_distro_cache_valid_time
rather than distro_cache_valid_time. Also, this
variable is only used by apt, not zypper.

Change-Id: I71682b7d6bf183967d06f485772760876e2c8df6
(cherry picked from commit 2820d9ec0b586aa26a777cafd5441cfe8bad5ebc)

[{'created': '2018-08-25 20:44:57.000000000', 'message': 'Upgrade pip/setuptools/wheel in the venv

To ensure a uniform experience across distributions
and from build to build, we need to ensure that the
venv has a consistent version of pip, setuptools and
wheel. This patch ensures that these packages are
upgraded to the latest version allowed by the args
provided.

This prevents issues as discovered and solved by
https://review.openstack.org/596553

We also remove the virtualenv_site_packages argument
from the pip tasks as they are unnecessary given that
the virtualenv is created in an earlier task.

Change-Id: Ia9e2f695212b01a54f8e73fbd03faa8e9b492f93
'}]
commit_message:
Upgrade pip/setuptools/wheel in the venv

To ensure a uniform experience across distributions
and from build to build, we need to ensure that the
venv has a consistent version of pip, setuptools and
wheel. This patch ensures that these packages are
upgraded to the latest version allowed by the args
provided.

This prevents issues as discovered and solved by
https://review.openstack.org/596553

We also remove the virtualenv_site_packages argument
from the pip tasks as they are unnecessary given that
the virtualenv is created in an earlier task.

Change-Id: Ia9e2f695212b01a54f8e73fbd03faa8e9b492f93

commit_message:
Resolve bug with long time for loading node group template page

In this patch I implement work with ajax for loading node group
template and simplify it process. If user click on tab for
configuration some process, sahara-dashboard send ajax-request
and load this tab.

Change-Id: Ied6733403ced3c2b2cddd92a81d5087e2c58e771
Closes-bug: 1430112

commit_message:
Adjust tenacity mock

Recent changes in tenacity have broken how we mock the wait call for the test.
This change mocks out the inspect.getargspec call that is used in tenacity to
fix our unit tests for now. I think it might be beneficial to not actually test
the retry functionality in the paunch unit tests as it seems to be more
of a test for tenacity than paunch.

Change-Id: I37b09694de3ec9f31a7b945d19a83527c915b759
Related-Bug: #1788802

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: Iba5a6c6137e512da637444940738f5084b99764e

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-27 20:11:32.000000000', 'message': "Move source build vars back to vars/main

All other roles have their pip_packages in defaults/main.yml
and the lists were all in vars/main.yml before [1] was
implemented. Since then, the py_pkgs lookup does not recognise
that neutron has the project_group of 'neutron_all', but
instead thinks it is in 'all'. This mismatches the git
repo project group, resulting in a failed repo build if the
group is not populated. It also results in neutron packages
building even if neutron is not configured to be part of the
build.

This patch moves the vars back to vars/main.yml to restore
proper functioning of the repo build and correct association
with the project group.

These vars are not used by the distro install process, so it
does not matter where they're sourced.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/573661

Change-Id: If8aa2dba6fc5b09a71c93de7f048ea716fc6a2c1
(cherry picked from commit c3b3e91e811cbb1ff7d00e3f61e76d4efa6f6cc0)
"}]
commit_message:
Move source build vars back to vars/main

All other roles have their pip_packages in defaults/main.yml
and the lists were all in vars/main.yml before [1] was
implemented. Since then, the py_pkgs lookup does not recognise
that neutron has the project_group of 'neutron_all', but
instead thinks it is in 'all'. This mismatches the git
repo project group, resulting in a failed repo build if the
group is not populated. It also results in neutron packages
building even if neutron is not configured to be part of the
build.

This patch moves the vars back to vars/main.yml to restore
proper functioning of the repo build and correct association
with the project group.

These vars are not used by the distro install process, so it
does not matter where they're sourced.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/573661

Change-Id: If8aa2dba6fc5b09a71c93de7f048ea716fc6a2c1
(cherry picked from commit c3b3e91e811cbb1ff7d00e3f61e76d4efa6f6cc0)

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-27 13:56:01.000000000', 'message': "Correct Hbase ports in Ambari plugin

port number for HBase configured in Sahara starts with 600xx
where as hortonworks ambari configures these ports on the
hbase master and region servers with 160xx.Although Ambari
will start the master server with the 160xx port, clients
can't connect them due to improper security rules.As a
result hbase master web info port link in the cluster
general info page doesn't work.HBase region server won't start.

This patch sets the HBase ports correctly for Ambari Plugin.

Change-Id: Ic13944ed729c0840578784f50a53f17b0706b62c
Story: #2003562
Task: #24853
(cherry picked from commit b248ef27e475020aa7087e2a8e7d07781d6f437c)
"}]
commit_message:
Correct Hbase ports in Ambari plugin

port number for HBase configured in Sahara starts with 600xx
where as hortonworks ambari configures these ports on the
hbase master and region servers with 160xx.Although Ambari
will start the master server with the 160xx port, clients
can't connect them due to improper security rules.As a
result hbase master web info port link in the cluster
general info page doesn't work.HBase region server won't start.

This patch sets the HBase ports correctly for Ambari Plugin.

Change-Id: Ic13944ed729c0840578784f50a53f17b0706b62c
Story: #2003562
Task: #24853
(cherry picked from commit b248ef27e475020aa7087e2a8e7d07781d6f437c)

commit_message:
pbrx-upload: remove final flag

This job isn't intended to be final (we expect jobs to set the
prefix flag).  But it also isn't safe to allow anyone to run,
so add allowed-projects.

Change-Id: I647f44deb2edc078eb88aad349df6afbdd0c37e2

commit_message:
Adds iPXE UEFI support to Multi Node AIO

Now expects a base URL that looks for iPXE files.  Uses
boot.ipxe.org by default but the base URL can be overridden to
point to custom compiled versions of ipxe.lkrn, ipxe.efi,
and undionly.kpxe.

Change-Id: Ib2c10c4817eaf9a78326f3de00aed0c16f8df776

that fixes it.

commit_message:
Don't trigger designate job on irrelevant change

The job 'neutron-tempest-plugin-designate-scenario' don't need
to be triggered on irrelevant change (i.e. docs). This patch
aligns the list of irrelevant files of designate job to other
tempest jobs.

Change-Id: Iee996d5d7d95b7e853d028a3ccc6035f3d8cc38f

commit_message:
Correct Hbase ports in Ambari plugin

port number for HBase configured in Sahara starts with 600xx
where as hortonworks ambari configures these ports on the
hbase master and region servers with 160xx.Although Ambari
will start the master server with the 160xx port, clients
can't connect them due to improper security rules.As a
result hbase master web info port link in the cluster
general info page doesn't work.HBase region server won't start.

This patch sets the HBase ports correctly for Ambari Plugin.

Change-Id: Ic13944ed729c0840578784f50a53f17b0706b62c
Story: #2003562
Task: #24853
(cherry picked from commit b248ef27e475020aa7087e2a8e7d07781d6f437c)

commit_message:
Move source build vars back to vars/main

All other roles have their pip_packages in defaults/main.yml
and the lists were all in vars/main.yml before [1] was
implemented. Since then, the py_pkgs lookup does not recognise
that neutron has the project_group of 'neutron_all', but
instead thinks it is in 'all'. This mismatches the git
repo project group, resulting in a failed repo build if the
group is not populated. It also results in neutron packages
building even if neutron is not configured to be part of the
build.

This patch moves the vars back to vars/main.yml to restore
proper functioning of the repo build and correct association
with the project group.

These vars are not used by the distro install process, so it
does not matter where they're sourced.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/573661

Change-Id: If8aa2dba6fc5b09a71c93de7f048ea716fc6a2c1

commit_message:
Add path to api-paste.ini in rdo

Using smart-sources[1] breaks neutron installation
in openstack-ansible-functional-distro_install-centos-7
job because the api-paste.ini file is placed in
/usr/share/neutron instead of /etc/neutron.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/588647/

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/596553
Change-Id: Idc23fbadff7b6d5490648910561a7356b5bee853

commit_message:
Use older keepalived version in functional tests

It looks that current keepalived version which is available in
Ubuntu Xenial repositories (1:1.2.24-1ubuntu0.16.04.1) is broken
and cause failure of some functional tests in Neutron.
Details are in [1].
Older version works fine so as temporary solution we can use
this version in functional tests.

This issue don't happens on master and stable/rocky branch, as there
newer cloud-archive repo is used and it has newer version of keepalived
which works fine.

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/keepalived/+bug/1789045

Change-Id: I30cf42c620d89266e772e97ba3255212530846d9
Closes-Bug: #1788185

subject: WIP: Nova-Cyborg workflow
messages:
[{'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-06-14 20:53:54.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2018-06-14 21:22:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

This could go into backlog specs, but you'll need to apply the template either way. Alternatively, you could put this in the nova docs under future things:

https://docs.openstack.org/nova/latest/reference/index.html#forward-looking-plans

I suggest the latter."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-06-14 21:33:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thanks Matt. I was really just looking for a way to get this sequence diagram out where people could look at it and discuss the flow.  I wasn't going to try to merge anything.  If we get to a point where this needs to merge somewhere, I expect Sundar will copy/paste it into a cyborg spec or something."}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-06-14 21:36:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 9708, 'date': '2018-06-15 13:46:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-06-15 13:56:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(3 comments)'}, {'account_id': 9708, 'date': '2018-06-15 15:11:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 21672, 'date': '2018-06-17 17:02:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Eric, thanks for taking this initiative. Here's the merged Rocky spec for os-acc where the discussion started: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/566798/ 

My main comment is that Cyborg can discover devices and resources. For attachments, Cyborg can either discover them (e.g. PCI functions) or have device drivers that help in creating/attaching them (e.g. mediated devices). So, there is no need for the user to run a command to create attachment UUIDs.

Here's my stab at the flow and design -- please review.
https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/os-acc-discussion
https://docs.google.com/drawings/d/1gbfimiyA1f5sTeobN9mpavEkHT7Z_ScNUqimOkdIYGA/edit 
(I am not familiar with the syntax to create sequence diagrams; hope public Google docs are ok.)"}, {'account_id': 21672, 'date': '2018-06-19 01:03:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Further IRC discussion today at: http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-nova/%23openstack-nova.2018-06-18.log.html#t2018-06-18T22:08:02 

In response to: "but that doesn't provide enough detail to say things like "I want SSLv3 offload accelerator vs. I want generic crypto accelerator" or something" -- that would be via traits. The RP has a function type trait of whatever granularity the device/driver supports.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2018-08-27 13:30:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 14070, 'date': '2018-08-27 19:34:42.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Sorry for the confusion, this was just intended as a placeholder until it got formalized into a cyborg spec.'}]

I focused on separating the concerns into their own methods. 

 1. get_etc_protocol_name_map: only knows about how to use getprotoent from python

 3. get_iptables_protocol_args: only knows about how iptables wants its protocol arguments

commit_message:
Use system protocol assigments for iptables protocol map

Merge the system protocol assignments into the iptables name
to protocol mapping array, IPTABLES_PROTOCOL_NAME_MAP, so that
systems with updated or new values in /etc/protocols can
successfully install iptables rules.

This was done as an IptablesFirewallDriver() instance mapping
since there is typically only a single instance per-agent,
and it also allows us to more easily unit test it.

Change-Id: Ib73def4e2a9e3644462fdee312768382fcb800a5
Closes-Bug: #1783378

commit_message:
Switch to stestr

According to Openstack summit session [1],
stestr is maintained project to which all Openstack projects should migrate.
Let's switch to stestr as other projects have already moved to it.

This change also fixes a bunch of D001 violations where lines are too
long in .rst documents.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/YVR-python-pti

Change-Id: Ic20ae60d9020896690c5e7f07124d7500ffd3d2d

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: Ib8b04669a50a84345f2ad8456a73473aec2df2f4
Story: #2002586
Task: #24337

commit_message:
Resolve duplicate service_type for service setup

While doing service setup, it would always deploy all services
with the same service type which means that the cloudformation
service would end up where the orchestration is.

This patch splits out each item to be it's own in order to avoid
this issue.

Change-Id: Ie664790421697a1f3fa3ccbd343d6f9fb9545161
(cherry picked from commit 0e9ab661bb8a261c2d9b87c3e939b34895f9dd45)

commit_message:
Resolve duplicate service_type for service setup

While doing service setup, it would always deploy all services
with the same service type which means that the cloudformation
service would end up where the orchestration is.

This patch splits out each item to be it's own in order to avoid
this issue.

Change-Id: Ie664790421697a1f3fa3ccbd343d6f9fb9545161

The patch needs to go to stable/rocky instead of master, with this in, master is broken for me.'}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2018-08-27 13:46:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: -Workflow

Actually after thinking about it a bit more, I'm confused as to why this is breaking for me locally but not in gate. See http://paste.openstack.org/show/728824/ for the error I'm seeing in my local run.

Pulling the +W for now."}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2018-08-27 15:07:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow+1

Comparing with the history for stable/queens, this patch definitively belongs into stable/rocky, so will proceed with the revert here.

The reasons that the issue was not noticed by our checks are:

a) The devstack* jobs disable tempest, where the error would manifest.
b) Zuul helpfully prepares all the needed repositories with all existing branches[0], while when devstack running alone it will clone only the branch that is needed.

[0] http://logs.openstack.org/76/596276/1/check/tempest-full/09ee516/job-output.txt.gz#_2018-08-24_10_40_53_032817'}]

subject: Add novajoin to _independent
messages:
[{'account_id': 9914, 'date': '2018-08-24 17:54:08.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 9914, 'date': '2018-08-24 17:55:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

Waiting for novajoin commit to merge.'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2018-08-24 18:07:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I don't see a novajoin repo nor novajoin team under governance:

http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/governance/tree/reference/projects.yaml

It will need to be proposed as an official team before we can handle its releases."}, {'account_id': 9914, 'date': '2018-08-24 18:34:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Workflow

Weird - I had thought we had gone through the process.  Just out of curiosity, I notice for instance that bandit is not in governance either.  Is that an oversight - or is it ok because Security is a valid team?'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2018-08-24 18:43:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hmm, good question. It appears it was official:

https://github.com/openstack/governance/blob/0aa4de942ade7bda5667add0a57c62d578c709db/reference/legacy.yaml#L1470'}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2018-08-24 18:44:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Sorry, got cut off.

It was official, but IIRC it was moved out of openstack (must have been after that last release) to be a broader python security linter and I believe they do their own releases now.'}, {'account_id': 9914, 'date': '2018-08-24 18:57:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

We were always going to be an unofficial project.  If openstack-releases only handles official projects, then we'll probably end up abandoming this review."}, {'account_id': 11904, 'date': '2018-08-24 19:01:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Yeah, sorry, the releases repo is only for officially governed projects. Other projects need to perform their own releases.

Pushing a tag to the repo does trigger zuul jobs, so in your case I believe that's all you need."}, {'account_id': 9914, 'date': '2018-08-27 18:00:42.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

we're going to continue to be unofficial."}]

Run bandit job with python3

Most jobs run with python3 now by default.

In addition, this commit moves bandit testenv definitions
before non-testenv tox environments. I believe this brings
better readability.

commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I88b61d1204048b36f24dce787be663de04b4c345
Story: #2002586
Task: #24322

commit_message:
Correct Hbase ports in Ambari plugin

port number for HBase configured in Sahara starts with 600xx
where as hortonworks ambari configures these ports on the
hbase master and region servers with 160xx.Although Ambari
will start the master server with the 160xx port, clients
can't connect them due to improper security rules.As a
result hbase master web info port link in the cluster
general info page doesn't work.HBase region server won't start.

This patch sets the HBase ports correctly for Ambari Plugin.

Change-Id: Ic13944ed729c0840578784f50a53f17b0706b62c
Story: #2003562
Task: #24853
(cherry picked from commit b248ef27e475020aa7087e2a8e7d07781d6f437c)

commit_message:
VMAX doc - important known issue

A ucode upgrade on an VMAX All Flash will cause issues if
workloads are leveraged. This known issue needs to be
documented until a fix is merged.

Change-Id: Iba8df9385b65f03c0ab9ea07a728e1ccd8e04e86

We need to use pydot rather than pydot3 because
of a broken version comparison in networkx, where it rejects
the lower version number of pydot3.

Without this patch the taskflow unit tests which use dot for
rendering graphics are no longer runnable.

Change-Id: I676e4d76627b3ecd0e4a9b896b2b93d652ebb25d
(cherry picked from commit 349f79937f681bc3da3c9c3b545c5714968c15f4)
'}]
commit_message:
Add pydot test dependency

We need to use pydot rather than pydot3 because
of a broken version comparison in networkx, where it rejects
the lower version number of pydot3.

Without this patch the taskflow unit tests which use dot for
rendering graphics are no longer runnable.

Change-Id: I676e4d76627b3ecd0e4a9b896b2b93d652ebb25d
(cherry picked from commit 349f79937f681bc3da3c9c3b545c5714968c15f4)

commit_message:
Fix provisioning failure with `ramdisk` deploy interface

Provisioning fails if ironic node is configured with ``ramdisk``
deploy interface and PXE boot config file is not present for the
node.

Task: #24817

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-25 19:25:05.000000000', 'message': 'Upgrade pip/setuptools/wheel in role test venv

In the integrated build, the repo build process upgrades
pip/setuptools/wheel in the venv to our preferred pinned
version, but developer mode does not.

Keystone requires the pysaml2 python library, which
requires setuptools > 30.3.0 - but CentOS only has 28.8.0
when it builds the venv, so the package install fails.

In this patch we create the venv, then upgrade pip,
setuptools and wheel, then install the keystone packages.

Doing this for all roles is impractical, but it will be
necessary to unblock patches from merging into roles today
and may be neceesary to port back to stable/rocky for the
same reason. In the future when we use the python_venv_build
role we can do all this there instead of repeating this patch
across all the roles.

Change-Id: I96434ccc7eb5f02e12605e378d733c39f092a411

commit_message:
Upgrade pip/setuptools/wheel in role test venv

In the integrated build, the repo build process upgrades
pip/setuptools/wheel in the venv to our preferred pinned
version, but developer mode does not.

Keystone requires the pysaml2 python library, which (from
4.6.0) due to [1] requires setuptools > 30.3.0 - but CentOS
only has 28.8.0 when it builds the venv, so the package
install fails.

In this patch we create the venv, then upgrade pip,
setuptools and wheel, then install the keystone packages.

Doing this for all roles is impractical, but it will be
necessary to unblock patches from merging into roles today.
In the future when we use the python_venv_build role we can
do all this there instead of repeating this patch across all
the roles.

[1] https://github.com/IdentityPython/pysaml2/commit/9c7b0014ccc4229031813ddcc5f6790b59540df5
Change-Id: I96434ccc7eb5f02e12605e378d733c39f092a411

commit_message:
Use noop-jobs for astara

These jobs are all failing and astara has not merged a single change
since October 2016. Use noop-jobs template here.

This is either the first step in retiring the repository or a way to
move the jobs in-repo where they can be enabled directly with testing.

Change-Id: Ie349751645bcd500be9eb20e06b06a384221dd4f

Skips signal handling on Windows

Setting up signal handling fails on Windows due to missing select
module attributes. This patch skips the setup on Windows.

Closes-Bug: #1788022

commit_message:
Use v2 api when talking to etcd

Use the etcd v2 api when talking to vault because there is a bug
in the client which causes vault  to be inaccessible if the first
etcd unit goes down.

Change-Id: Iadbfcb9998d029cc6cf599008c124960993acb4e
Closes-Bug: 1782620

commit_message:
Revert "Fail if the Overcloud inventory is empty"

This reverts commit 773bef1c7a5e7015c4df42ce23e2f9c8c158f424.

The reverted commit made the inventory fail if there was no overcloud
deployed. However, the inventory is also used a lot in cases with no
overcloud (many validations for instance).

Change-Id: I19a4e02d25037f54c2449396ea84492b49555fd6
(cherry picked from commit d96473bb3bb22ab36300250eefd3b0a67ceb61af)

commit_message:
Update zuul layout to disable voting on python2 jobs for rocky/stein

The tox job fails on python 2 and as we're moving forward python3 we
don't need this job anymore.
Run it voting on queens and pike only.

Change-Id: I700386571e0ec5eafafa35cfcfc2bb50c485aca2

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I1f88ff4b1b290a165958223f9aeb28c12f1cab96

specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project

normalized.
